\begin{center}
\vspace{-5mm}
\begin{tcolorbox}[
    colback=gray!3,         % 更淡的背景色，减少视觉压力
    colframe=gray!40,        % 边框颜色变淡
    arc=1.5mm,               % 稍微圆润一点的圆角
    boxrule=0.6pt,           % 细边框更显精致
    width=1.0\linewidth,
    left=2pt, right=2pt, top=2pt, bottom=2pt,
    boxsep=2pt
]
\begin{minipage}[t]{0.20\linewidth}
\vspace{0pt}
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=\linewidth]{figs/first_clip.png}
    \vspace{1mm}
    \includegraphics[width=\linewidth]{figs/second_clip.png}
\end{minipage}
\hfill
\begin{minipage}[t]{0.79\linewidth}
\vspace{0pt}
\tiny
\textbf{Question.}
Which object is less likely to change shape if you attempted to cut it?
\textbf{Description:}
In the first clip, a person with long, dark, matte nails is holding a decorative light bulb. The light bulb made of glass and metal is illuminated with a purple hue and has a holographic effect inside, creating a shimmering appearance. The person rotates the light bulb, showcasing its design and the light it emits. In the second clip, a hand is holding a red, textured object that resembles a piece of candy or a similar material. The hand uses a small knife to cut into the object, revealing its interior which appears to be a smooth, gel-like substance.
\textbf{Thinking:} The light bulb in the first clip is a rigid object made of glass and metal, which would likely shatter or break if cut. The candy-like object in the second clip, however, is flexible and can be cut without changing its overall shape significantly, as it is designed to be cut and consumed. Given this analysis, the object that is least likely to change shape if cut is the candy-like object in the second clip.
\end{minipage}
\end{tcolorbox}
\vspace{-5mm}
\end{center} 为什么会这样，我想让右侧文字和左侧第一张图片顶部对齐

你现在写法里虽然两个 `minipage` 都用了 `[t]`，但**右侧 minipage 里你又加了 `\vspace{0pt}`**，这会在 minipage 顶部人为插入一段“不可忽略的竖直材料”，导致 TeX 的对齐参考点发生偏移，于是看起来右侧文字整体被“往下顶了一点”，就出现了你截图里的效果。

另外，右侧用了 `\tiny`，`minipage` 顶部的基线/行距计算也会让这种偏移更明显。

## 解决办法（推荐）
把右侧（甚至左右两侧）的 `\vspace{0pt}` 去掉即可：

```latex
\begin{minipage}[t]{0.20\linewidth}
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=\linewidth]{figs/first_clip.png}
    \vspace{1mm}
    \includegraphics[width=\linewidth]{figs/second_clip.png}
\end{minipage}
\hfill
\begin{minipage}[t]{0.79\linewidth}
\tiny
\textbf{Question.}
...
\end{minipage}
```

通常这样右侧第一行就会和左侧第一张图的顶部对齐。

## 如果你确实需要“消除顶部空白”
有些人加 `\vspace{0pt}` 是为了去掉列表/段落等带来的顶端空白，但在这里反而坏事。更稳的写法是：**在 minipage 开头用 `\leavevmode` 或直接不插任何竖直命令**。例如：

```latex
\begin{minipage}[t]{0.79\linewidth}
\leavevmode
\tiny
...
\end{minipage}
```

## 仍不齐时的“硬对齐”手段
如果你的图片文件本身上方有留白（png 常见），那即便排版对齐了，看起来也会不齐。这时应当裁掉图片留白：

```latex
\includegraphics[width=\linewidth,trim=0 10 0 0,clip]{figs/first_clip.png}
```

`trim=左 下 右 上`，把“上”适当加大即可。

如果你愿意，把 `first_clip.png` 顶部留白情况（或原图）描述一下/发图，我可以帮你估一个合适的 `trim` 数值。
